Interface IMarketDataEntitlementsService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IComponent, IHasAttributes, IService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MarketDataEntitlementsServiceBase

    public interface IMarketDataEntitlementsService
extends IService, IComponent
    Interface required by any service used to check whether or not incoming FIX market data subscription requests should be allowed.

    • Method Detail

      • checkEntitlements

        void checkEntitlements(IConnectionPoint cp,
                       IFIXMessage subscriptionRequest,
                       IMDSmartFIXMessageFactory smartFIXMessageFactory)
                throws MessageProcessorRejectException
        Check whether the FIX session indicated by the given connection point is entitled to make the given subscription request.
        Parameters:
        cp - Connection point of FIX session on which subscription request was received.
        subscriptionRequest - FIX market data subscription request to be checked against entitlements.
        smartFIXMessageFactory - used to create the reject message (if needed)
        Throws:
        MessageProcessorRejectException - if not entitled. Exception contains a suitable FIX reject message.

      • checkEntitlements

        void checkEntitlements(IConnectionPoint cp,
                       String symbol,
                       String marketDepth,
                       boolean aggregated,
                       IFIXMessage subscriptionRequest,
                       IMDSmartFIXMessageFactory smartFIXMessageFactory)
                throws MessageProcessorRejectException
        Check whether the FIX session indicated by the given connection point is entitled to make the given subscription request for the symbol and associated request properties. This interface provides per symbol validation and allows one reject message to be generated for each invalid symbol.
        Parameters:
        cp - Connection point of FIX session on which subscription request was received.
        symbol - Symbol requested.
        marketDepth - Market depth requested.
        aggregated - Whether aggregated or detailed data requested.
        subscriptionRequest - The complete subscription request message (should any further information be required by implementation.)
        smartFIXMessageFactory - used to create the reject message (if needed)
        Throws:
        MessageProcessorRejectException - If the symbol is not entitled. Exception contains a suitable FIX reject message.
